{"key":"processedPost-6177700","value":{"id":6177700,"first":6176992,"last":6178109,"when":1161093201,"utime":"10/17/06 04:53 PM","content":"Most electric heaters have a switch so you don't have to run them on 1500 watt.  If it has a 400 watt setting, that would be plenty.<br /><br />Never use a heating pad to heat a fruiting chamber, because the temperature differential will cause all your humidity to condense on the sides of the FC.  Use a heater to heat the entire area if necessary.  Low 70's is perfect.<br />RR","title":"Re: Heating A FC","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}